You are extending the SoStudy platform with a Tutoring Activation system.

IMPORTANT
Do NOT modify the existing authentication system.
The registration flow is already finished.

Tutoring is NOT enabled during registration.

Tutoring must now be activated AFTER login inside the student profile.

--------------------------------------------------

CORE IDEA

The platform has two states for students:

1. BASIC USER (no tutoring activated)
2. TUTORING USER (tutoring service activated)

Many features belong to the tutoring service and must be disabled in BASIC mode.

--------------------------------------------------

FEATURES THAT BELONG TO TUTORING SERVICE

The following areas are part of the tutoring service and should NOT be fully accessible in BASIC mode.

They should appear as locked or preview features.

HOME SCREEN

- Your Tutors
- Extra Sessions
- Recently Viewed Documents
- Meetings
- Chat (all chats except the AI learning assistant)

PROFILE SCREEN

- Set Availability
- My Subjects
- Extra Hours

--------------------------------------------------

BASIC USER EXPERIENCE

If the student has NOT activated tutoring:

Instead of the tutoring features, show a large call-to-action section:

"Activate Tutoring"

This CTA should appear:

- on the Home screen
- inside the Profile tutoring section

The locked features may show preview UI cards but must display:

"Activate tutoring to access this feature."

The preview cards must not contain real data.

--------------------------------------------------

TUTORING ACTIVATION FLOW

When the student clicks:

"Activate Tutoring"

Start a multi-step onboarding flow.

STEP 1

Choose tutoring type:

- Online Tutoring
- Local Tutoring

STEP 2 (only if Local Tutoring selected)

Partner Search

User enters location or city.

Show available tutoring partners.

User selects a partner institute.

STEP 3

Subject Selection

The student can see a list of all available school subjects.

The student selects the subjects where tutoring is needed.

STEP 4

Send Tutoring Request

The student submits a tutoring request.

After submission show confirmation message:

"Your tutoring request has been sent."

Explain that the tutoring institute will contact the student via phone or email.

Also show the tutoring contact details:

- Phone number
- Email address

Add button:

"Understood"

--------------------------------------------------

POST REQUEST STATE

After the request has been submitted:

The student returns to the Home screen.

The CTA must change from:

"Activate Tutoring"

to

"Request Submitted"

The user must still be able to view the tutoring institute contact details at any time.

Add a section:

"Your Tutoring Request"

Display:

- Partner Name
- Phone Number
- Email Address

--------------------------------------------------

PROTOTYPE TESTING FEATURE

For prototyping and testing purposes only:

Add a temporary button inside the student Profile screen:

"Accept Tutoring Request (Prototype)"

This button simulates the tutoring institute approving the request.

This button must ONLY exist for prototyping.

When clicked:

The system switches the user state from:

BASIC USER → TUTORING USER

--------------------------------------------------

TUTORING USER STATE

When tutoring is activated:

Unlock all tutoring features:

HOME

- Your Tutors
- Extra Sessions
- Recently Viewed Documents
- Meetings
- Chat

PROFILE

- Set Availability
- My Subjects
- Extra Hours

These features should now behave as normal interactive components.

--------------------------------------------------

STATE MANAGEMENT

Use a tutoring status state for the user.

Possible values:

tutoringStatus =

notActivated
requestSent
activated

The UI must update dynamically based on this state.

--------------------------------------------------

UX GOALS

The tutoring activation must feel simple and intuitive:

Profile
→ Activate tutoring
→ Choose online or local
→ Select subjects
→ Send request
→ Wait for approval
→ Tutoring features unlock

--------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT

Do NOT modify:

AuthWrapper
Login system
Registration system

Only implement the tutoring activation system after login.